Day 11 — JFrog Pipelines and CI/CD Integration
JFrog Pipelines
A CI/CD orchestration system natively integrated with Artifactory. Pipelines are defined in YAML and are aware of Artifactory resources — artifacts, builds, and release bundles.

Core Concepts
Resources — Inputs and outputs of pipeline steps:

GitRepo — a Git repository
BuildInfo — a build published to Artifactory
ArtifactoryGenericRepo — artifacts in Artifactory
ReleaseBundle — a signed, immutable bundle of artifacts
PropertyBag — key-value store passed between steps
Steps — Units of work in a pipeline:

Bash — run arbitrary shell commands
MvnBuild, GradleBuild, NpmBuild — native build steps
DockerBuild, DockerPush — container steps
XrayScan — trigger a security scan
PromoteBuild — promote build from one repo to another
Pipelines — sequences of steps with resource triggers.

GitHub Actions Integration
- uses: jfrog/setup-jfrog-cli@v4
  with:
    jfrog-url: ${{ secrets.JF_URL }}
    oidc-provider-name: github
    oidc-audience: jfrog

- run: jf mvn-config --repo-resolve-releases libs-release --repo-deploy libs-snapshot
- run: jf mvn clean install
- run: jf rt build-publish

Release Bundles
A Release Bundle is a signed, immutable, verified collection of artifacts representing a release candidate:

Cryptographically signed — tamper-proof
Version-controlled
Can be distributed to edge nodes via JFrog Distribution
The canonical artifact of a release
